Perturbed Inertial Krasnoselskii-Mann Iterations

We run all the different accelerations on an image of dimension $512\times 512$, with $50\%$ of its pixels randomly erased, with a maximum number of iterations of $100$ and a tolerance of $10^{-3}$. We select a step size of $\rho=1.8$ and a relaxation parameter of $\lambda=0.8$, a regularisation parameter $\sigma=0.5$, and execute the iterations. This runs in a few minutes. And as a final step, we visualize the results and plot the convergence plots.
